    <div class="container">
        <div class="intro">
            <p>Built this converter after a member asked about switching between different salts in recipes.</p>
            
            <p>Here's the thing: not all salt weighs the same. Table salt is dense and fine, so it packs tight. Kosher salt has larger, flaky crystals with more air between them. Sea salt falls somewhere in the middle, depending on how it's processed.</p>
            
            <p>That means 1 teaspoon of table salt â‰  1 teaspoon of kosher salt. If you're swapping one for the other without adjusting, you can end up with bread that's either bland or way too salty.</p>
            
            <p>This tool does the math for you. Plug in what the recipe calls for, choose your salt type, and it'll tell you exactly how much to use.</p>
        </div>
        
